frameDefinitions: A Topical_entity has properties which are affected by the existence and association of an Entity.
A Recipient comes into possession of the Theme as a result of the joint action of the Donor and the Recipient.
A Protagonist is awake at some Time and Place.

The words in this frame describe situations in which a Perpetrator forcibly seizes control over a Victim's Vehicle to gain some end.  '' 'French farmers have hijacked a lorry and destroyed its load of strawberries.'
Two or more distinct entities, which may be concrete or abstract objects or types, are characterized as being similar to each other.
An Agent has an Attribute which can take different Values, and the Agent selects and then begins to use some Value for that Attribute.
frameExamples: By the 1920s a characteristic book <t>had</t> black and white photographic illustrations only .
I <t>recieved</t> a box from him in the mail.
French farmers have <t>hijacked</t> a lorry and destroyed its load of strawberries.

A mulberry is very <t>similar</t> in shape
to a loganberry
They scoff at their opponents and <t>assume</t> an air of superior knowledge
listRoleDefinitions: Some entity, abstract or concrete, which is stated to exist and be associated with the <fen>Topical_entity</fen>.
The entity under discussion, whose states and properties are impacted by its association with the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Entity</fen> exists and is associated with the <fen>Topical_entity</fen>
The place where the <fen>Entity</fen> is associated with the <fen>Topical_entity</fen>.
The person who acts to come into possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The person who gives the <fen>Theme</fen> to the <fen>Recipient</fen>.
The entity that changes possession, beginning in the possession of the <fen>Donor</fen> and ending up with the <fen>Recipient</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Recipient</fen> comes into possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The location at which the Recipient comes into possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The entity that is not sleeping.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Protagonist</fen> is awake.
Where the event takes place.
This is the person (or other agent) who forcibly seizes control over a vehicle to gain some end.
This is the means of transportation which gets under the control of the perpetrator. Example: The terrorists hijacked <fex name='Vehicle'>the plane</fex>.
This role describes the people that are suffering as a result of the <fen>Perpetrator</fen>'s action.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
This role marks constituents that express the set of objects or types whose similarity is at issue.

When there is an asymmetry, <fen>Entity_1</fen> is the entity characterized by its similarity to <fen>Entity_2</fen>, whose characteristics are assumed to be known.  <fen>Entity_1</fen> is often an external argument.

When the <fen>Entities</fen> are expressed separately, <fen>Entity_2</fen> is the one whose characteristics are assumed to be known; it serves as a basis for establishing characteristics of <fen>Entity_1</fen>.
This role marks constituents which express a property in respect to which the similarity of the entities is assessed.
A fact about <fen>Entity_1</fen> or the <fen>Entities</fen> that reveals how <fen>Entity_1</fen> is the same or different from other entities.  (Note the contrast with 'as to'.)
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the similarity occurs or exists.
The Place is the general area in which similarity occurs or exists
The <fen>Agent</fen> selects a <fen>Value</fen> for his/her <fen>Attribute</fen> and begins to use it.
The <fen>Attribute</fen> of the <fen>Agent</fen> can take on several <fen>Value</fen>s, selected by the <fen>Agent</fen> .
The <fen>Value</fen>, chosen and made effective by the <fen>Agent</fen>, specifies the <fen>Attribute</fen>.
The time period when the <fen>Agent</fen> selects and begins to put into effect the <fen>Value</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Agent</fen> has the <fen>Attribute</fen> which can take different <fen>Value</fen>.
listRoleExamples: She received the package <fex>before the month was out</fex>.
<fex>She</fex> was awake through the whole football game.
The rebels skyjacked a plane <fex>with 89 passangers</fex>.
<fex>The two painters</fex> were alike in being unable to draw acceptably .
In the first phase <fex>Barthes's approach</fex> has similarities to that of Levi-Strauss.
The results of Method 2 show remarkable similarity <fex>to those obtained by Method 1</fex>
The disc announced Friday is <fex>physically</fex> similar to current music CDs
His presidency was different <fex>in that it offered a way forward for the common man</fex> .
<fex>Some organizations, like the Sierra Club</fex>, have adopted a position of neutrality on US immigration policies.
The Council of Constance (1414-18) adopted conciliarism <fex>as a stance</fex>, hoping that it would permit the election of a pope acceptable to both Catholic factions.
He crammed his cap back again into his pocket and re-entered the office, assuming <fex>an air of absentmindedness</fex>.
<fex>On January 1, 2001</fex>, our nation will adopt the US dollar as our official currency.

sourceCandidateSpans.text: Hoback in Q: Into the Storm
